> Because you want to add pages, change fonts, and rewrite content dynamically, the current [index.html](file:///Users/queenhannah/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/hannah-portfolio/index.html) will be retrofitted. It will load, fetch your custom settings from the database, and inject the content into the existing beautiful animation structure.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Infrastructure (Node.js + Express)
- Initialize a `package.json` in the project root.
- Install `express`, `sqlite3` (database), `multer` (for media uploads), and `passport-google-oauth20` (for Gmail login).
- Create `server.js` to serve the site and provide API routes.

### Database Schema (SQLite)
Use a lightweight SQLite file database (`portfolio.db`) with tables:
- **Users**: (Only your authorized email will be allowed).
- **Theme Settings**: (Colors, font URLs, background images).
- **Page Content**: (Headlines, body copy, media links for each chapter/section).
- **Receipts**: (Dynamic list of achievements).
- **Speaking/Events**: (Dynamic list).

### Admin Panel ("The Backdoor")
- **Route**: GET `/admin` (Protected)
- A clean, user-friendly dashboard (React or Vanilla JS) where you can:
  - Update HEX color codes / font links.
  - Upload images, voice memos (`.mp3`/`.wav`), or videos.
  - Paste YouTube/Vimeo embed links.
  - Edit the text for the Home, Journey, and Impact sections.
  - Add new "Receipt" cards.

### Frontend API Integration
- Modify [index.html](file:///Users/queenhannah/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/hannah-portfolio/index.html) and [app.js](file:///Users/queenhannah/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/hannah-portfolio/app.js) to make a `fetch('/api/content')` call on load.
- Dynamically apply CSS variables to the `:root` pseudo-class for color/font overrides.
- Dynamically render the DOM elements for chapters and receipts based on the database response, preserving the Scrollytelling scroll-triggers.

